Minnesota Power and Light Co israising 55 mln dlrs through an offering of first and refundingmortgage bonds due 1994 with a 7-3/4 pct coupon and parpricing, said sole manager PaineWebber Inc.    That is 68 basis points more than the yield of comparableTreasury securities.    Non-callable for five years, the issue is rated A-2 byMoody's Investors Service Inc and A-plus by Standard and Poor'sCorp. Reuter&#3;